@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p class="text-muted"><em>Last updated: May 2026</em></p>

<p>
    This Privacy Policy explains what FindActivity ("we", "us") collects when you use the site,
    how we use it, and the choices you have. We try to keep this short and in plain English.
</p>

<h2>What we collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account details</strong> you give us at signup: email address, password (hashed, never stored in plain text), date of birth, and any display name or bio you choose to add.</li>
    <li><strong>Activity content</strong> you create or post: titles, descriptions, addresses or general locations, dates, and any participation/review you make.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical data</strong>: IP address, browser type, and basic logs we keep to operate the service and prevent abuse.</li>
    <li><strong>Cookies</strong>: a session cookie used to keep you signed in. We don't use third-party advertising trackers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How we use it</h2>
<ul>
    <li>To run the service: showing activities, letting you join or host them, sending account-related email (signup, password reset, event reminders).</li>
    <li>To enforce our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Terms">Terms</a> and <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="CommunityGuidelines">Community Guidelines</a>, including verifying you meet the minimum age (18).</li>
    <li>To respond when you contact us or submit a report.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What we don't do</h2>
<ul>
    <li>We don't sell your personal information.</li>
    <li>We don't share your email address with other users; only your display name appears publicly on activities and reviews.</li>
    <li>We don't show ads.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Service providers</h2>
<p>
    We use a small number of providers to operate the service. The Mapbox Geocoding API powers
    address autocomplete and the map &mdash; addresses you type may be sent to Mapbox under their
    terms. We use SendGrid for transactional email (signup, password reset, notifications).
    Providers process your data only as needed to provide their service to us.
</p>

<h2>Your choices</h2>
<ul>
    <li>You can change your password and edit your profile in the account area.</li>
    <li>You can delete your account at any time. Deleting your account removes your profile and personal information; activities and reviews you authored may remain visible in anonymized form so other users' history isn't broken.</li>
    <li>To request a copy of your data, or to ask us to delete it, email us at the contact below.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Children</h2>
<p>FindActivity is for adults only. You must be at least 18 to create an account.</p>

<h2>Changes</h2>
<p>
    If we make material changes to this policy we'll update the "Last updated" date above and,
    where appropriate, notify you by email or in the app before the changes take effect.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Questions or requests: <a href="mailto:privacy@findactivity.local">privacy@findactivity.local</a></p>

<p class="text-muted">
    <small>This page is a starter draft. Replace the contact email and refine the language with your lawyer before launch.</small>
</p>
